original: Ljungkvist, Axel Johannes, kyrkoherde, Vartofta, f. 10/8/90 i Skarstad, Skarab. 1. G. 21 m. Kerstin Helena Lönneroth. Barn: Ingrid f. 22, Rune 28. — Stud:ex. i Skara 13, teol. fil. ex. i Gbg 15, teol kand. o. prakt. teol. prov i Upps. 18, prästv. i Skara s. å. Tjg. i Alingsås, pred. v. Bolltorps S’an. 18, kommin. i Grevbäck 20, i Falköp. 26, pred. v. länslas. 25-31, timlär. v. samrealsk. 25-28, kyrkoh. i Slöta fr. 32. Ordf. i Slöta, Karleby, Mularps o. Ti-arps kyrko-st., kyrkoråd, i Slöta ’skoil-styr. o. Karleby skolråd.
translated: Ljungkvist, Axel Johannes, clergyman, Vartofta, born on October 8, 1890 in Skarstad, Skaraborg county. 1st marriage in 1921 with Kerstin Helena Lönneroth. Children: Ingrid, born in 1922, Rune, born in 1928. Education: graduated from Skara high school in 1913, received a Bachelor of Theology from Gothenburg in 1915, completed practical theology examinations in Uppsala in 1918, ordained as a priest in Skara the same year. Served in Alingsås, preached at Bolltorp Church in 1918, served as a curate in Grevbäck from 1920, in Falköping from 1926, preached at the county asylum from 1925-1931, taught part-time at the secondary school from 1925-1928, became the vicar in Slöta from 1932. Chairman of Slöta, Karleby, Mularp, and Tiarp parish council, member of the school board in Slöta, and Karleby school council.
